Distribution. A relatively common nycteribiid with a southerly distribution, mainly in the Balkans, Apennines and Iberian Peninsula, with scattered records in Central Europe (
Szentiványi et al. 2016
) and common also in Africa. In Romania it has been recorded all over the country, with 31 distinct geographical records altogether.
